Sentencas: In this work, a microtubular cell consisting of a thin Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (GDC) electrolyte (thickness: below 10 mu m) on a support NiO/GDC anode (1.8 mm outer diameter, 200 mu m wall thickness) with a La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta/GDC functional cathode has been developed for intermediate/low temperature operation.
Titulo: Development of Ceria Based SOFCs With a High Performance La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95-Ag Composite Cathode

Sentencas: The functional cathode was prepared by in situ infiltrating the electrochemically catalytic nano-Ag particles into the as-established 20 mu m thick cathode.
Titulo: Development of Ceria Based SOFCs With a High Performance La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95-Ag Composite Cathode

Sentencas: The as-proposed Ag-impregnation route ensures a very homogeneous particle dispersion and a good adhesion of Ag to the ceramic matrices.
Titulo: Development of Ceria Based SOFCs With a High Performance La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95-Ag Composite Cathode

Sentencas: The cells were successfully operated to produce the maximum power densities of 0.41 W cm(-2) (1.27 A cm(-2), 0.32 V), 0.83 W cm(-2) (2.23 A cm(-2), 0.37 V), and 1.05 W cm(-2) (2.39 A cm(-2), 0.44 V) at 450 degrees C, 500 degrees C, and 550 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Development of Ceria Based SOFCs With a High Performance La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95-Ag Composite Cathode
